{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781544835701,"sessionID":"ses_133a85052ffepoFnn6mX54vd0x","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_sS6tXQXUX5iRyBpghI2QakHs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"parent-skill|sk-skill-parent|create_parent_skill_","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create","include":"*.txt"},"output":"Found 9 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/README.txt:\n  Line 44: | **parent-skill** | `/create:sk-skill-parent <skill-name> [create\\|update] [--modes <m1,m2,...>] [--path <dir>] [:auto\\|:confirm]` | Scaffold a parent skill with nested mode packets (one hub `graph-metadata.json`, `mode-registry.json` source of truth, N `deep-<mode>` packets, non-discoverable `shared/`) |\n\n  Line 69: ├── parent-skill.md       # /create:sk-skill-parent command\n\n  Line 81:     ├── create_parent_skill_auto.yaml\n\n  Line 82:     ├── create_parent_skill_confirm.yaml\n\n  Line 133: /create:sk-skill-parent my-loop-workflows create --modes research,review,ai-council :confirm\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_parent_skill_presentation.txt:\n  Line 1: # /create:sk-skill-parent Presentation Contract\n\n  Line 3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:sk-skill-parent`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, and result display. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n  Line 30: Restart with: @markdown /create:sk-skill-parent <skill-name> [create|update]\n\n  Line 37: For `:auto`, resolve setup using the system auto-mode contract, then load `create_parent_skill_auto.yaml` only when every required field is available.\n","metadata":{"matches":9,"truncated":false},"title":"parent-skill|sk-skill-parent|create_parent_skill_","time":{"start":1781544835656,"end":17815448