{"type":"text","timestamp":1781544896144,"sessionID":"ses_133a85052ffepoFnn6mX54vd0x","part":{"id":"prt_ecc59881a001jbpnNDf7Aif1vK","messageID":"msg_ecc592663001ykklOVXhaWxD2T","sessionID":"ses_133a85052ffepoFnn6mX54vd0x","type":"text","text":"{\"seat\":\"G1\",\"slice\":\"155 A5 stale post-rename docs\",\"findings\":[{\"id\":\"G1-1\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"packet\":\"155\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/155-parent-nested-skill-pattern/003-formalize-pattern/implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":\"20\",\"title\":\"Implementation summary key_files points at removed command path\",\"evidence\":\"Line 20 quotes stale key_files entry: `- \\\".opencode/commands/create/parent-skill.md\\\"`. Actual command is now `.opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md`: `.opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md:7` quotes `# /create:sk-skill-parent Router` and line 45 quotes `canonical /create:sk-skill-parent entrypoint`. Glob confirmed only `.opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md` exists for `*parent*` command markdown.\",\"why\":\"This is a broken `key_files` path, not just stale prose; resume/review consumers following the packet metadata land on a non-existent file.\",\"fix\":\"Replace `.opencode/commands/create/parent-skill.md` with `.opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md` in the implementation-summary `_memory.continuity.key_files` block.\"},{\"id\":\"G1-2\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"packet\":\"155\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/155-parent-nested-skill-pattern/003-formalize-pattern/implementation-summary.md\",\"line\":\"3,58,100\",\"title\":\"Implementation summary still names the old /create:parent-skill command\",\"evidence\":\"Line 3 quotes `the /create:parent-skill scaffolder`; line 58 quotes ``/create:parent-skill` scaffolder` and `commands/create/parent-skill.md`; line 100 quotes `The `/create:parent-skill` `update` branch`. Actual router says `/create:sk-skill-parent` at `.opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md:7` and line 45.\",\"why\":\"The shipped command was renamed after these docs were written, so packet completion docs now advertise the wrong operator entrypoint.\",\"fix\":\"Update these references to `/create:sk-skill-parent` and `commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md`, preserving only intentionally legacy asset filenames if they remain.\"},{\"id\":\"G1-3\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"packet\":\"155\",\"file\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/155-parent-nested-skill-pattern/spec.md\",\"line\":\"72\",\"title\":\"Parent spec says sk-doc section §21, but shipped section is §10\",\"evidence\":\"Line 72 quotes `sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md §21 + parent-skill hub/registry templates`; the same parent spec line 92 quotes `Formalize: sk-doc §10 + hub/registry templates`, and the actual shipped heading is `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:1018` `## 10. PARENT SKILLS WITH NESTED MODE PACKETS`.\",\"why\":\"This is doc staleness in the parent spec: one scope bullet points reviewers to a non-shipped section number while the completed phase and actual sk-doc file use §10.\",\"fix\":\"Change the parent spec line 72 reference from `§21` to `§10`.\"},{\"id\":\"G1-4\",\"severity\":\"P2\",\"packet\":\"155\",\"file\":\".opencode/commands/create/sk-skill-parent.md\",\"line\":\"7,15,16,17\",\"title\":\"Command rename left internal asset names on create_parent_skill_*\",\"evidence\":\"Line 7 quotes `# /create:sk-skill-parent Router`, while lines 15-17 route to `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_parent_skill_presentation.txt`, `create_parent_skill_auto.yaml`, and `create_parent_skill_confirm.yaml`. The YAML assets themselves now declare `# Entrypoint: /create:sk-skill-parent` at `create_parent_skill_auto.yaml:5` and `create_parent_skill_confirm.yaml:5`.\",\"why\":\"This does not break routing because the router points at the existing assets, but it leaves an internal naming mismatch that will keep surfacing as stale-looking `parent_skill` references after the command was renamed to `sk-skill-parent`.\",\"fix\":\"Either rename the three assets to `create_sk_skill_parent_*` and update router/index references, or explicitly document that `create_parent_skill_*` is retained as an internal legacy asset stem.\"}]}","time":{"start":1781544880154,"end":1781544896142},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f97a3a88423b8ba016a3037b01b788191b39034912b83deea","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
